### A2. Variant snapshot is internally inconsistent with W1

The Variant still says:

```yaml
heresy_families_without_ci_detector: 31
```

while the Phase A checkpoint claims W1 shipped a detector manifest + CI discovery job.

This counter is not sound as written. Either:

- W1 reduced “families without CI discovery detector” to 0, in which case the variant is stale; or
- the counter actually means “families without fail-on-regression enforcement,” in which case the name and Phase A interpretation are wrong; or
- the mission intended one detector row per H001-H031 family, in which case W1 is incomplete because the manifest/script currently emit aggregate rows, not all H001-H031 IDs individually.

Evidence:

- `docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md:442-452`:
  - `heresy_families_without_ci_detector: 31`
  - other Phase A counters are reduced to 0
- `docs/definitions/og-dolt-heresy-completion-2026-07-08.md:528-537` says W1 creates/checks H001-H031 discovery patterns in CI.
- `docs/heresy-detectors.md:21-34` contains aggregate manifest rows:
  - H001-H005
  - H006-H008/H014
  - H009/H022
  - H010/H024/H026
  - H011/H012
  - H019
  - H027
  - H028
  - H029
  - H030
  - H031
  - framing
- `scripts/check-heresies.sh --report /tmp/heresy-detector-report.json` exited 0 and emitted 12 report rows, including:
  - H030 `total_hits: 14`
  - H031 `total_hits: 198`
- Missing as individual detector IDs if the bar is “H001-H031 coverage”: H013, H015-H018, H020-H021, H023, H025, plus H024a/H024b are represented only indirectly by H010/H024/H026.

Required fix:

- Define the counter’s semantics and update it.
- If Phase A’s bar is discovery-only CI reporting, set the variant to reflect CI discovery coverage and leave fail-on-regression explicitly deferred.
- If Phase A’s bar is per-heresy-ID coverage, add/rename detector rows so every H001-H031 family is accounted for.

